FACEBOOK’S CRYPTOCURRENCY, Libra, has suffered setbacks in recent weeks, as the company’s founder Mark Zuckerberg appears before a congressional committee to defend it. The Economist’s technology editor Tim Cross explains what’s at stake. We explore how a giant timber mill in Finland is leading the way in sustainable forestry. And Damian Bradfield, chief creative officer of WeTransfer, on how ethics and the internet can coexist, based on his latest book “The Trust Manifesto”. Kenneth Cukier hosts. Runtime: 21 min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn